{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-list-template-tsx","path":"/2017/page/2","result":{"data":{"site":{"meta":{"title":"Raw SAS - SAS Tips n Tricks","description":"Tips n Tricks and other SAS Titbits from around 10 years of SAS projects and tinkering about with SAS"}},"remark":{"posts":[{"post":{"html":"<p>If you’ve ever done any moderate googling on a SAS topic you’ve probably unearthed a thread on SAS-L, quite possibly from several decades ago.  You’d be forgiven for assuming that this simply something that “used to exist’ because - up until recently - that’s exactly what I thought too.</p>\n<p>Well - how wrong I was.  SAS-L is still alive and kicking.  The “L” stands for listserv, and is a mail server run by the University of Georgia.  It’s basically a spamming service for SAS issues (am sure there is a better word for it though).</p>\n<p>Getting started is as easy as 1,2,3:</p>\n<p>1 - Sign up to the listserv service: <a href=\"https://listserv.uga.edu/cgi-bin/wa?GETPW1\">https://listserv.uga.edu/cgi-bin/wa?GETPW1</a>\n2 - Verify your email\n3 - Subscribe to SAS-L  mailing list: <a href=\"https://listserv.uga.edu/cgi-bin/wa?SUBED1=sas-l\">https://listserv.uga.edu/cgi-bin/wa?SUBED1=sas-l</a></p>\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 300px; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 95.74468085106382%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Screen 2BShot 2B2017 05 11 2Bat 2B23 52 27 300x287\" title=\"Screen 2BShot 2B2017 05 11 2Bat 2B23 52 27 300x287\" src=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/94d19c68972e8f77c43774c5555e04e0/5a46d/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-05-11-2Bat-2B23.52.27-300x287.png\" srcset=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/94d19c68972e8f77c43774c5555e04e0/4dcb9/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-05-11-2Bat-2B23.52.27-300x287.png 188w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/94d19c68972e8f77c43774c5555e04e0/5a46d/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-05-11-2Bat-2B23.52.27-300x287.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></div>\nThere is a ton of information on SAS-L on <a href=\"http://www.sascommunity.org/wiki/SAS-L\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">sasCommunity</a>, and even a dedicated sugi <a href=\"http://www2.sas.com/proceedings/sugi28/247-28.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">paper</a>. &#xA0;So get involved - and you could be the next Rookie of the Year!\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 300px; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 73.40425531914893%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Image 2Buploaded 2Bfrom 2BiOS 300x221\" title=\"Image 2Buploaded 2Bfrom 2BiOS 300x221\" src=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/6546e51f03fae89f09640c1a4e13b7c2/f93b5/Image-2Buploaded-2Bfrom-2BiOS-300x221.jpg\" srcset=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/6546e51f03fae89f09640c1a4e13b7c2/bc01b/Image-2Buploaded-2Bfrom-2BiOS-300x221.jpg 188w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/6546e51f03fae89f09640c1a4e13b7c2/f93b5/Image-2Buploaded-2Bfrom-2BiOS-300x221.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\n&#xA0;","frontmatter":{"title":"SAS L is StiLL aLive","path":"/sas-l-is-still-alive/","previewImg":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.0471204188481675,"src":"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/e2698d9b23cf98909cac2538ebe4ed33/ee604/frontmatter14.png","srcSet":"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/e2698d9b23cf98909cac2538ebe4ed33/69585/frontmatter14.png 200w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/e2698d9b23cf98909cac2538ebe4ed33/497c6/frontmatter14.png 400w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/e2698d9b23cf98909cac2538ebe4ed33/ee604/frontmatter14.png 800w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/e2698d9b23cf98909cac2538ebe4ed33/0fba7/frontmatter14.png 872w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"tags":["SQL"],"date":"May 12, 2017"}}},{"post":{"html":"<p>Tabs or Spaces?  Does it even matter, so long as you / your team are consistent?  For many SAS developers the standard place to write code is the Program Editor - for which the default setting is to use tabs, else 4 spaces.</p>\n<p>Interestingly - the generated code in Enterprise Guide and DI Studio uses 3 spaces.</p>\n<p>My preference is 2 spaces, but what do you think is the most commonly used approach out there?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ukupat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Uku Pattack</a> has created a <a href=\"https://ukupat.github.io/tabs-or-spaces/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">github page</a>  which may settle (or inflame!) this classic Holy War.  It scans all github repos (over 1 star) for .sas files, and checks the tab vs space usage.  Here are the results:</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 273px; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 110.10638297872339%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Screen 2BShot 2B2017 03 02 2Bat 2B20 43 56 273x300\" title=\"Screen 2BShot 2B2017 03 02 2Bat 2B20 43 56 273x300\" src=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/9c1fcb6564d5e8fc4a950a3a3f67a57e/0217c/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-03-02-2Bat-2B20.43.56-273x300.png\" srcset=\"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/9c1fcb6564d5e8fc4a950a3a3f67a57e/4dcb9/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-03-02-2Bat-2B20.43.56-273x300.png 188w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/9c1fcb6564d5e8fc4a950a3a3f67a57e/0217c/Screen-2BShot-2B2017-03-02-2Bat-2B20.43.56-273x300.png 273w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 273px) 100vw, 273px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<p>So - which do you think was most popular?  The choices are:</p>\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\n<ul>\n \t<li>8 spaces</li>\n \t<li>4 spaces</li>\n \t<li>3 spaces</li>\n \t<li>2 spaces</li>\n \t<li>Tabs</li>\n</ul>\n<div>Head over to Uku's <a href=\"https://ukupat.github.io/tabs-or-spaces/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">site</a> to find out!</div>\n<div></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Tabs v Spaces - which is more popular in SAS?","path":"/tabs-v-spaces/","previewImg":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":0.9090909090909091,"src":"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/f43ab3858364ef51042b232748963077/cfb1b/frontmatter15.png","srcSet":"/tetrahex-rawsas/static/f43ab3858364ef51042b232748963077/69585/frontmatter15.png 200w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/f43ab3858364ef51042b232748963077/497c6/frontmatter15.png 400w,\n/tetrahex-rawsas/static/f43ab3858364ef51042b232748963077/cfb1b/frontmatter15.png 758w","sizes":"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px"}}},"tags":["Programming","sas"],"date":"Mar 02, 2017"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"page":"year","archives":{"2012":8,"2013":10,"2014":4,"2015":7,"2016":17,"2017":12,"2018":9,"2019":2,"2020":3},"filter":{"frontmatter":{"date":{"gte":"2017","lt":"20171"}}},"limit":10,"skip":10,"numPages":2,"currentPage":2,"year":"2017"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}